{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01G4Xt9N9gMjE4ZskbrB3XEi","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a complete picture of the current spark-pi namespace configuration. Let me summarize what I found:\n\n**Deployments:**\n- `spark-master`: image `apache/spark:3.5.3`, resources: limits cpu=500m/mem=1Gi, requests cpu=200m/mem=512Mi, 1 replica\n- `spark-worker`: image `apache/spark:3.5.3`, resources: limits cpu=500m/mem=1Gi, requests cpu=200m/mem=512Mi, 1 replica; env SPARK_WORKER_MEMORY=1G, SPARK_WORKER_CORES=1\n- `spark-pi` job runs the SparkPi application with local mode using 2 cores, 512MB driver memory, and 1000 iterations, with the same resource constraints\n\nThe namespace also has RBAC configured with a ServiceAccount, Role granting permissions on services, configmaps, volumes, and pods, and a RoleBinding connecting them together. There's currently one spark pod running.\n\nNow I need to create a migration and upgrade plan. Since the configuration has already been customized from defaults with specific resource limits, image versions, RBAC policies, and job parameters, I should document a sensible upgrade strategy covering image version updates, resource adjustments, and verification steps for each phase. Composing the maintenance plan...","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1194,"cache_read_input_tokens":33072,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1194},"output_tokens":12,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"770e2ab4-39d6-4e1b-ae5d-e5e00c822bea","uuid":"edee7db3-5e53-4def-b7f9-6cd3cd423435","request_id":"req_011Cc2iMX8mhimkTMGiAR9Wm"}
