{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01G4Xt9N9gMjE4ZskbrB3XEi","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01HkMeLWTrncqsTYoSY8Qo97","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"cat > /tmp/plan.md << 'PLAN_EOF'\n# Spark-Pi Namespace — Maintenance Upgrade Plan\n\n**Namespace:** spark-pi  \n**Prepared:** 2026-06-14  \n**Status:** DRAFT — for team review; no changes applied yet\n\n---\n\n## Current State Summary\n\n| Resource | Image | CPU Req/Limit | Memory Req/Limit |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| spark-master (Deployment, 1 replica) | apache/spark:3.5.3 | 200m / 500m | 512Mi / 1Gi |\n| spark-worker (Deployment, 1 replica) | apache/spark:3.5.3 | 200m / 500m | 512Mi / 1Gi |\n| spark-pi (Job, driver) | apache/spark:3.5.3 | 200m / 500m | 512Mi / 1Gi |\n\n**RBAC:** ServiceAccount `spark-pi` bound to Role `spark-pi-role`  \n(verbs: create/get/list/watch/delete/update/patch on pods, services, configmaps, pvcs)\n\n**Job parameters:** `--master local[2]`, `--driver-memory 512m`, 1000 Pi iterations,  \n`backoffLimit: 0` (no retries on failure)\n\n**Notable observations:**\n1. The spark-pi Job uses `--master local[2]` (local in-process mode), bypassing the\n   deployed spark-master/spark-worker cluster entirely. This is the primary configuration\n   gap to address.\n2. `SPARK_WORKER_MEMORY=1G` env on the worker matches the memory limit (1Gi), leaving no\n   headroom for the JVM overhead — OOM risk under load.\n3. Image `apache/spark:3.5.3` is current in the 3.5 line; a patch-level upgrade to\n   3.5.4 (when released) or a minor upgrade to 3.6.x may be desired.\n4. The Role grants `delete` on pods and `update`/`patch` on pods/services, which is\n   broader than a typical read-only job driver needs.\n\n---\n\n## Upgrade Plan\n\n### Phase 1 — Pre-Upgrade Validation (no changes)\n\n**Goal:** Confirm baseline health before touching anything.\n\nSteps:\n1. Verify all pods are Running and Ready:\n   ```\n   kubectl get pods -n spark-pi\n   ```\n2. Confirm the spark-pi Job completed successfully (exit code 0):\n   ```\n   kubectl get job spark-pi -n spark-pi\n   kubectl logs -n spark-pi -l job-name=spark-pi\n   ```\n3. Record current resource usage as a baseline:\n   ```\n   kubectl top pods -n spark-pi\n   ```\n\n**Verification:** All 3 pods (master, worker, job driver) show Ready. Job pod exit code 0.\n\n---\n\n### Phase 2 — Fix Job Master URL (local → cluster mode)\n\n**Why:** `--master local[2]` ignores the deployed spark-master/spark-worker cluster. For\na real distributed workload the driver must connect to `spark://spark-master:7077`.\n\n**Change:** Update the spark-pi Job spec:\n```yaml\n# Before\n--master local[2]\n# After\n--master spark://spark-master:7077\n```\nAlso update `--driver-memory` from `512m` to `768m` (headroom inside the 1Gi limit).\n\n**Order:** Delete the existing completed/running Job, then re-apply the updated manifest.\nThe Job is not a Deployment; it must be recreated.\n\n**Verification:**\n```\nkubectl get job spark-pi -n spark-pi   # status.succeeded = 1\nkubectl logs -n spark-pi -l job-name=spark-pi | grep \"Pi is roughly\"\n```\nLook for the Pi approximation log line from a distributed execution (tasks will show\nworker assignments instead of local thread names).\n\n---\n\n### Phase 3 — Worker Resource Adjustment\n\n**Why:** `SPARK_WORKER_MEMORY=1G` matches the 1Gi memory limit, leaving zero headroom\nfor the JVM itself. The pod will be OOM-killed under sustained load.\n\n**Change:** Update the spark-worker Deployment:\n```yaml\n# env: keep SPARK_WORKER_MEMORY=1G unchanged (this is Spark's executor memory)\nresources:\n  requests:\n    cpu: \"200m\"\n    memory: \"1280Mi\"   # up from 512Mi\n  limits:\n    cpu: \"1000m\"       # up from 500m\n    memory: \"1536Mi\"   # up from 1Gi — headroom for JVM overhead above SPARK_WORKER_MEMORY=1G\n```\n\n**Order:** `kubectl apply` the updated Deployment; the rolling update restarts the worker\npod with the new limits while the master remains live.\n\n**Verification:**\n```\nkubectl rollout status deployment/spark-worker -n spark-pi\nkubectl top pod -l app=spark-worker -n spark-pi\n```\nWorker pod should stabilize Running without OOMKilled events:\n```\nkubectl get events -n spark-pi --field-selector reason=OOMKilling\n```\n\n---\n\n### Phase 4 — Master Resource Adjustment\n\n**Why:** Symmetric with the worker change; current 500m CPU limit may throttle GC under\nconcurrent submissions.\n\n**Change:** Update the spark-master Deployment:\n```yaml\nresources:\n  requests:\n    cpu: \"250m\"\n    memory: \"512Mi\"\n  limits:\n    cpu: \"1000m\"       # up from 500m\n    memory: \"1Gi\"      # unchanged\n```\n\n**Order:** After Phase 3 completes. Apply and wait for rollout.\n\n**Verification:**\n```\nkubectl rollout status deployment/spark-master -n spark-pi\nkubectl get pods -n spark-pi -l app=spark-master\n```\n\n---\n\n### Phase 5 — Image Upgrade (Spark 3.5.3 → target version)\n\n**Why:** Stay current on security and bug-fix patches.\n\n**Target image:** `apache/spark:3.5.4` (or the then-current 3.5.x patch tag — confirm\navailability on Docker Hub before the change window).\n\n**Change:** Update image in all three resources (spark-master Deployment, spark-worker\nDeployment, spark-pi Job template):\n```yaml\nimage: apache/spark:3.5.4   # was 3.5.3\n```\nAlso update the jar path in the Job command if it embeds the version string:\n```\n# Before\n/opt/spark/examples/jars/spark-examples_2.12-3.5.3.jar\n# After\n/opt/spark/examples/jars/spark-examples_2.12-3.5.4.jar\n```\n\n**Order:**\n1. Pull and verify the new image tag is available: `docker pull apache/spark:3.5.4`\n2. Apply spark-worker Deployment first (workers are stateless).\n3. Apply spark-master Deployment.\n4. Re-create the spark-pi Job with the updated image.\n\n**Verification:**\n```\nkubectl get pods -n spark-pi -o jsonpath='{.items[*].spec.containers[*].image}'\n```\nAll pods should report the new image tag. Re-run the Job and confirm Pi output.\n\n---\n\n### Phase 6 — RBAC Tightening\n\n**Why:** `spark-pi-role` grants `delete`, `update`, and `patch` on `pods`, and `delete`\non `services` — unnecessary for a compute-only driver that only needs to watch cluster\nstate.\n\n**Change:** Update the Role rules to remove unnecessary verbs:\n```yaml\nrules:\n- apiGroups: [\"\"]\n  resources: [\"pods\", \"services\", \"configmaps\"]\n  verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]\n- apiGroups: [\"\"]\n  resources: [\"persistentvolumeclaims\"]\n  verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\"]\n```\n(Retain `create` on PVCs only if dynamic volume provisioning is used by jobs; remove if not.)\n\n**Order:** Last — apply after all compute changes are verified working, so a permissions\nregression does not block earlier verification steps.\n\n**Verification:**\n```\nkubectl auth can-i delete pods --as=system:serviceaccount:spark-pi:spark-pi -n spark-pi\n# Expected: no\nkubectl auth can-i get pods --as=system:serviceaccount:spark-pi:spark-pi -n spark-pi\n# Expected: yes\n```\n\n---\n\n## Rollback Procedure\n\nEach phase is independently reversible:\n- **Phases 2–5 (Deployments):** `kubectl rollout undo deployment/<name> -n spark-pi`\n- **Phase 2 (Job):** Delete the re-created Job and re-apply the original manifest with\n  `--master local[2]`.\n- **Phase 6 (RBAC):** Re-apply the original Role manifest restoring the broader verbs.\n\nKeep a copy of all original manifests (`kubectl get -o yaml`) before the change window.\n\n---\n\n## Change Window Checklist\n\n- [ ] Phase 1: Pre-upgrade validation passed\n- [ ] Phase 2: Job master URL updated; Pi output confirmed from cluster workers\n- [ ] Phase 3: Worker limits raised; no OOMKill events\n- [ ] Phase 4: Master limits raised; rollout complete\n- [ ] Phase 5: Image upgraded to 3.5.4 (or target); jar path updated; job re-run passes\n- [ ] Phase 6: RBAC tightened; `can-i` checks pass\n- [ ] Post-change: `kubectl top pods -n spark-pi` baseline recorded for comparison\nPLAN_EOF\necho \"Plan written: $(wc -l /tmp/plan.md | awk '{print $1}') lines, $(wc -c /tmp/plan.md | awk '{print $1}') bytes\"","description":"Write the migration plan to a temp file"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1194,"cache_read_input_tokens":33072,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1194},"output_tokens":12,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"770e2ab4-39d6-4e1b-ae5d-e5e00c822bea","uuid":"4cb19210-229d-477d-a656-3dbebdb8a28d","request_id":"req_011Cc2iMX8mhimkTMGiAR9Wm"}
